# Data Studio — Cursor Rules

**Read STATE.md first.** It is the single source of truth — data model, roadmap, locked decisions, database inventory. Read CONTRIBUTING.md for how to run things. Everything under docs/archive/ is historical and should not be trusted as current.

## Model policy

Use Sonnet for anything that matters: architecture, multi-file edits, agent scripts, data integrity. Use Opus when planning cross-codebase refactors or schema decisions. Only use lighter models for trivial single-line changes. Optimize for value, not cost.

## Autonomy

Run everything without asking. Stop and confirm only for destructive operations (delete, drop, force-push), public commits, or anything that touches production or spends money. Always check `git status` before committing — another session may be editing the same repo.

## Critical rules (full list in STATE.md)

- Never use the word "engine" in code, comments, or docs.
- FDIC amounts are in thousands — multiply by 1000 on ingest.
- Canadian CU annual reports are in thousands of CAD — multiply by 1000.
- `cert_number >= 900001` for Canadian credit unions.
- Don't store PDFs. Extract, use the source URL, delete the file.
- Use `upsert` with `onConflict` for all ingestion. Scripts must be rerunnable.
- `npm run build` passes before every commit. No `any`, no `@ts-ignore`.
- Don't target Brim's existing clients in BD output (list in STATE.md).
